  "texts": [
    "Significant differences were found between adversarial testing 23 and human-in-the-loop and guardrails and human-in-the-loop (corrected p = 0.0067).",
    "In evaluating deployed LLMs (Fig. 5e), the most common assessments focused on hallucinations or disinformation (50.0%) and robustness (38.9%).",
    "However, 19.4% (7/36) of respondents indicated no evaluations had been conducted.",
    "Cochran's Q Test revealed significant variation in the importance of these evaluations (Q = 77.1, p < 0.0001), with post-hoc analysis (Supplementary Table 15) showing significant differences between explainability and prompt injection (i.e., a technique where specific prompts or questions are used to trick the GenAI into bypassing its specified restrictions, revealing weaknesses in how it understands and responds to information), and between fairness versus ideological leaning and prompt injection (corrected p = 0.0040).",
    "Integrating GenAI into healthcare presents several challenges (Fig. 5f), with technical architecture and deployment cited most frequently (72.2%)."
  ]
}